children.text: The ceiling insulation has not been secured with fixed guards around the downlights, which may allow it to move and make contact with hot surfaces that could result in a fire.
The relevant Australian Standard AS 3900 Bulk Thermal Insulation states in section 5.3.2.2 that

‘In roof spaces with pitched roofs with flat ceilings it shall be ensured that areas adjacent to hot surfaces, such as recessed luminaires, hot fluids, built-in appliances and areas of high air movement, such as exhaust fans shall be fitted with guards’ .
The insulation needs to be installed under the heater platform to achieve the required R-value across the entire ceiling area.
